ces in this time of unprecedented economic and political uncertainty. Her book is a must-read for everyone concerned with health policy, international relations, and Third World societies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aMedical assistance, CubanxPolitical aspects. 0aMedical carexPolitical aspectsxCuba. 0aMedical carexPolitical aspectszCuba. 0aMedical policyxCuba. 0aMedical policyzCuba. 0aSymbolism in politicsxCubaxCuba. 0aSymbolism in politicszCuba. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520913950?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520913950423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520913950/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles